2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a microgrid ramping-oriented optimal scheduling model, which may involve the use of AI techniques for optimization. 
3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper discusses the use of distributed microgrids for supply-load balancing, which involves distributed computing and communication. 
4. cs.ET (Emerging Technologies): The paper discusses the use of renewable generation and microgrids, which are considered emerging technologies in the field of power systems. 
5. cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper may involve the development and implementation of software tools for microgrid control and optimization.
